b'Project Officer Job Summary Background and Context
UNESCO is the specialized agency of the United Nations with a mandate in education, science, culture, communication and access to information. It is one of the largest players in culture and cultural heritage in Afghanistan and supports the government in its endeavour to preserve the country\xe2\x80\x99s heritage and promote nation-building.
Within this overall framework, UNESCO is currently undertaking a number of different cultural programs, aimed at supporting the relevant Afghan authorities in their efforts to protect and promote Afghanistan culture in all its dimensions.
UNESCO is looking for a committed Project Officer who will provide specialized analytical advice to UNESCO Kabul Culture Unit with specific regard to tangible heritage, urban planning in historical cities and other architecture-related tasks.
Duties and Responsibilities
Under the overall authority of the Director of the Kabul Office, overall supervision of the Head of Culture Unit and direct supervision of the Project Manager the Project Officer  will take the following responsibilities: 
- Coordinate activities undertaken in cooperation with government agencies, international and national organizations relating to the implementation of tangible heritage and architecture-related tasks, including undertaking missions as necessary and requested by the Project Manager;
- Contribute to the planning of  CLT projects in historical-cultural contexts, especially in Bamiyan and Herat. This will include facilitating the Team\xe2\x80\x99s coordination with all the local governmental agencies and local stakeholders (shuras, communities) involved in the plans and ensure proper monitoring is done for the plans\xe2\x80\x99 concerned activities, including regular reporting to the Project Manager;
- Participate in provincial meetings and field missions as required in order to facilitate the work of UNESCO experts and staff in the field; 
-  Organize workshops and conferences related to tangible heritage, planning in historical contexts and architecture, including activities related to the UNESCO CLT support to Universities in Afghanistan (especially in Kabul, Herat and Bamiyan); 
- Organization of awareness raising campaigns, public events and promotional activities done by UNESCO for the promotion within local communities of activities related to the promotion of tangible heritage and/or architecture-related initiatives; 
- Perform any other tasks assigned by the Project Manager. Architecture Education
\xe2\x80\xa2 Masters in urban planning, architecture, conservation of tangible heritage and/or related fields 
Work Experience
\xe2\x80\xa2 At least 2-years relevant experience in urban planning, architectural and cultural projects; previous experience in dealing with local relevant authorities and institutions, including Universities, will be considered an asset;
\xe2\x80\xa2 Previous experience with UN Agencies and/or UNESCO would be considered as an asset.'

b'Water Management Specialist Job SummaryPart A: On-Farm Water Management 
1. Carrying out social mobilization for the establishment of Irrigation Associations (IAs) in the Project Areas, including, inter alia, the provision of: (a) training to communities in organization and management of IAs; (b) facilitation services for communities to develop the IAs\xe2\x80\x99 internal legal rules and regulations (by-laws); (c) assistance to IAs in order for them to be registered under the Water Law (1388); and (d) technical training to IAs regarding water distribution, maintenance of irrigation infrastructure, irrigation methods, water-saving techniques, crop-water requirements, and good agronomic practices.
2. (a) Carrying out rehabilitation works to small irrigation schemes or tertiary canals (watercourses) covering approximately 40,000 hectares in total in the Project Areas, including, inter alia: (a) rehabilitation of existing intakes, (b) canal lining; (c) construction of control structures and outlets; (d) construction of, culverts, laundry basins and cattle troughs; and
(b) Improving design standards and strengthening the private sector\xe2\x80\x99s capacity for contract management and construction techniques.
3. Establishing easily accessible pilot irrigation demonstration sites in the Project Areas to showcase improved water management practices/technology and agronomic water saving techniques/measures, as well as proper farm planning and layout for an efficient use of irrigation water.
Part B: Institutional Strengthening and Capacity Building of MAIL
 Developing the institutional capacity of MAIL to plan, design, implement and monitor irrigation programs, including, inter alia: (a) construction and/or renovation of  office buildings, one each in Kabul, Jalalabad, Baghlan, Mazar-e-Sharif and Herat, respectively for MAIL and Project  staff; (b) strengthening of MAIL\xe2\x80\x99s  Directorate of Irrigation at national, provincial and district levels; (c) strengthening the legal framework for the irrigation sector, (d) developing a national irrigation program, (e) undertaking of technical training in the irrigation sector including study tours transferring on-farm water management know-how; and (f) developing a database covering irrigation systems throughout the country.
Part C: Project Management, Coordination, Monitoring & Evaluation
 Strengthening the institutional capacity of MAIL for Project implementation, policy development, and technical innovation, monitoring and evaluation, by establishing and maintaining a Project Implementation Unit comprised of a Kabul-based core team, five (5) Project Area Teams and internationally recruited experts.
Part D: Support for Productivity Enhancement
1. Establishing easily accessible pilot irrigation demonstration sites in the Project Area to showcase improved water management practices/technology and agronomic water saving techniques/measures, improved agronomic and social management practices, as well as proper farm planning and layout for an efficient use of irrigation water.
2. Promoting land leveling and high-efficiency irrigation technologies in the Project Area.
3. Establishing Information Centers for farmers at the provincial and district level in the Project Area. \xe2\x80\xa2 Assume overall responsibility of the water management aspects of the region , and provide direction, supervision to the technical team;
\xe2\x80\xa2 Coordinate all implementation activities among the team members;
